The paper deals with image deblurring using convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of neural networks for this task also involves machine learning techniques, which falls under the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper specifically focuses on traffic surveillance images, which could fall under multimedia (cs.MM) or information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
